  "prompt": "Are there any other straight men diagnosed with histrionic personality disorder?",
  "response": "Histrionic Personality Disorder (HPD) can occur in individuals of any gender, including straight men. While the diagnosis has been more commonly associated with women in clinical literature, men can also be diagnosed with HPD. The characteristics of HPD, such as a pervasive pattern of excessive emotionality and attention-seeking behavior, can manifest in various ways regardless of gender. \n\nHowever, specific case studies or personal accounts of straight men with HPD may not be widely publicized due to the stigma associated with mental health disorders or the less frequent discussion of men's mental health issues. If you are looking for more information or resources on this topic, it may be helpful to consult mental health professionals or literature that discusses personality disorders across different demographics.",
